[𝐒𝐩𝐥𝐮𝐧𝐤 𝐒𝐈𝐄𝐌 𝐇𝐨𝐦𝐞 𝐋𝐚𝐛]💥Instruction/build below:👇 👇 👇

This home-lab will help you set up your own SOC at $0 by utilizing free trial software.

This is the most powerful home-lab focused on setting up Splunk SIEM and real-world use cases. If you’re interested in becoming a SOC Analyst(Tier 1/2), this lab will help you with SOC tools, rules, queries, apps, and integration.

Full credit goes to Rajneesh G. for making this content.

🟢 𝐏𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐎𝐒
📌 Download Virtualbox - https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads
📌 Download Windows Server 2019 [FREE TRIAL 180 days] - https://info.microsoft.com/ww-landing-windows-server-2019.html

🟢 𝐒𝐞𝐭 𝐮𝐩 𝐒𝐩𝐥𝐮𝐧𝐤 𝐒𝐈𝐄𝐌
📌 Download Splunk Enterprise [FREE TRIAL 60 days] - https://www.splunk.com/en_us/download/splunk-enterprise.html
📌 Download Splunk Security Essentials App [FREE] - https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/3435

🟢 𝐒𝐚𝐦𝐩𝐥𝐞 𝐒𝐞𝐜𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐭𝐲 𝐃𝐚𝐭𝐚𝐬𝐞𝐭
📌 BOTS V2 Dataset [16.4 GB]. - https://lnkd.in/dhJDy9fG
📌 BOTS V2 Dataset(Attack Only) [3.2 GB] - https://lnkd.in/ds2uuTm6

🟢 Top 20 Use Cases
You can go through the list of Splunk queries, detection rules and playbook here: https://research.splunk.com/detections/
Top 20 Detection rules below:
⭐ 𝐌𝐮𝐥𝐭𝐢𝐩𝐥𝐞 𝐅𝐚𝐢𝐥𝐞𝐝 𝐋𝐨𝐠𝐢𝐧𝐬: Detect multiple failed login attempts within a short time frame from a single source IP.
⭐𝐔𝐧𝐮𝐬𝐮𝐚𝐥 𝐀𝐜𝐜𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐭 𝐀𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐯𝐢𝐭𝐲: Monitor for unusual activities, such as excessive failed logins or multiple password changes within a short time for a specific user.
⭐𝐁𝐫𝐮𝐭𝐞 𝐅𝐨𝐫𝐜𝐞 𝐀𝐭𝐭𝐚𝐜𝐤: Look for repeated login failures across multiple accounts within a specific time window.
⭐𝐏𝐫𝐢𝐯𝐢𝐥𝐞𝐠𝐞𝐝 𝐀𝐜𝐜𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐭 𝐔𝐬𝐚𝐠𝐞: Monitor privileged account logins and actions to identify any unauthorized or unusual activities.
⭐𝐌𝐚𝐥𝐰𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐀𝐫𝐭𝐢𝐟𝐚𝐜𝐭𝐬: Search for known malware file hashes, filenames, or command-and-control IP addresses.
⭐𝐎𝐮𝐭𝐛𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐝 𝐃𝐚𝐭𝐚 𝐄𝐱𝐟𝐢𝐥𝐭𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧: Detect large data transfers to external destinations that may indicate data exfiltration.
⭐𝐈𝐧𝐛𝐨𝐮𝐧𝐝 𝐒𝐮𝐬𝐩𝐢𝐜𝐢𝐨𝐮𝐬 𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐟𝐟𝐢𝐜: Look for unexpected incoming traffic from suspicious IP addresses or geolocations.
⭐𝐀𝐧𝐨𝐦𝐚𝐥𝐨𝐮𝐬 𝐍𝐞𝐭𝐰𝐨𝐫𝐤 𝐓𝐫𝐚𝐟𝐟𝐢𝐜: Identify unusual network traffic patterns, such as spikes or deviations from baseline.
⭐𝐒𝐮𝐬𝐩𝐢𝐜𝐢𝐨𝐮𝐬 𝐔𝐬𝐞𝐫-𝐀𝐠𝐞𝐧𝐭 𝐒𝐭𝐫𝐢𝐧𝐠𝐬: Identify potentially malicious user-agent strings used in web requests.
⭐𝐑𝐚𝐧𝐬𝐨𝐦𝐰𝐚𝐫𝐞 𝐀𝐜𝐭𝐢𝐯𝐢𝐭𝐲: Detect ransomware indicators like file renames with specific extensions or ransom notes.

